Mount Monadnock. Within a year he had rebuilt the family's finances as a New York stockbroker.","number":1},{"category":"business","header":"He built 'Samarkand,' a vast Carolina farm","body":"Naming it for the Asian city his father had visited, Raphael Welles built Samarkand, a two-thousand-acre showplace in the North Carolina sandhills. He set out twenty-four thousand peach trees and bred horses before failed crops forced him to sell.","number":2},{"category":"religion","header":"A Bahá'í who spoke for the faith","body":"From 1938 Raphael Welles lectured on the Bahá'í Faith across New York and as far as Idaho, and in 1948 served as a Bahá'í delegate to a United Nations religious conference. His parents had hosted 'Abdu'l-Bahá in 1912.","number":3}],"sources":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[{"type":"in_law","related_id":"X03114","display_label":"was his father-in-law; Union general who led troops into Richmond"}],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"Raphael Welles","last_name":"Pumpelly","married_names":[],"display_name":"Raphael Welles Pumpelly","gender":"male","photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780758541/18514327_1449951758_fascop.jpg"},"military_service":[],"slug":"raphael-welles-pumpelly-1881"},"I01543":{"id":"I01543","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1883,"month":6,"day":3,"city":"New York","state":"New York","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1963,"month":9,"day":27,"city":"Los Angeles","state":"California","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":true,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_progenitor":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"notable":{"is